                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="12">
                                    <p>The manuscript is written in long lines; The Calendar has 16
                                        ruled lines per page whereas The Book of Hours has 12 ruled
                                        lines to the page: <dimensions type="written" scope="all">
                                            <height>600</height>
                                            <width>380</width>
                                        </dimensions>.</p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="miniature">
                                <p>
                                    <locus>13v</locus>: <dimensions type="written" scope="all">
                                        <height>650</height>
                                        <width>400</width>
                                    </dimensions>
                                    <title>Virgin and child</title>: Mary sitting on a throne with
                                    the Infant Jesus in her lap; the faces are almost completely
                                    effaced. Painted in a Flemish style c.1390-1400 with a 'Pink
                                    canopy', but ornamented with a Dutch border with gilded
                                    treefoils in penwork.</p>
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote type="mixed">
                                <p>Gilted major initials and painted borders. Painted textframes at
                                    the beginning of every hour. Minor gilded initials over 2 lines
                                    with simple penwork alternating in red and blue ink. Lombards in
                                    one line alternating blue and red.</p>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions>
